# API integration — Postman as source of truth

When integrating API endpoints into this repo (API client, hooks, pages, or server actions), **always** use the Postman collection as the single source of truth.

## Reference file

- **Path:** `postman/Practo CMS V2 — Complete (Part 1 + Part 2).postman_collection.json`
- **Scope:** Part 1 — Script workflow (Phases 1–3). Part 2 — Video workflow (Phases 4–5: First Line Up, First Cut, approve/reject).
- **Phase 6 — Final Package Delivery (per-video flow):** `postman/Phase 6 — Final Package Delivery (Per-Video Flow).postman_collection(1).json` — single `video` on create; add video; patch package name; presigned upload-url; per-video `resubmit-video` / `resubmit-metadata`; per-video approve/reject; per-thumbnail review; per-video withdraw (Super Admin only); get package/video(s), versions, queue (returns **videos**), stats, my-reviews. Product and workflow rules: `.cursor/rules/phase-6-final-package-delivery.mdc`.
- **Phase 7 — Language packages:** `postman/Phase7_Language_Packages_Postman.json` — prefix `/api/language-packages`; responses often use `{ success, data }`; optional thumbnails; Brand + Approver flow (`BRAND_REVIEW` → `AWAITING_APPROVER` → `APPROVED`). Integration notes: `Phase7_Frontend_Integration_Guide.md`.

## What to do

1. **Before implementing or calling any backend API**, read the relevant request(s) from this Postman collection.
2. **Use the collection for:** HTTP method, path, path params, query params, request body shape, and required headers (e.g. `Authorization: Bearer {{token}}`).
3. **Base URL:** Prefer env-based config (e.g. `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL`). The collection documents Cloudflare and direct-IP URLs; do not hardcode them.
4. **Auth:** Login is `POST /api/auth/login`; token is returned and must be sent as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on other requests.

## Collection structure (high level)

- **Auth:** Login (role-specific), Get Me, Forgot/Reset/Change Password
- **Users (Super Admin):** List, Get profile, Get by ID, Create, Update role, Toggle status
- **Scripts — CRUD:** Create, List, Get by ID, Update, Reviews history, My queue/approved/rejected, Search (by status)
- **Scripts — Workflow:** Submit, Approve, Reject, Submit revision, Lock, Unlock (Super Admin)
- **Videos (Part 2):** Upload URL, Register video, Approve, Reject (Medical Affairs & Content/Brand)
- **Packages / Phase 6:** See Per-Video Flow collection above (not in Part 1+2 JSON)
- **Language packages / Phase 7:** See Phase 7 collection above
- **Medical Affairs Fan-out Emails:** List, Add, Remove
- **Comments:** Get, Add, Update, Delete
- **Notifications:** Get mine, Unread count, Mark read / Mark all read
- **Audit Logs:** All, By script, By user
- **Health:** Health check, Root

When adding or changing API integration code, open the collection and align method, path, and payload with the corresponding request(s) in this file.
